# Testing Rules
- Use **React Testing Library**; prefer `user-event` over `fireEvent`.
- Test primary flows, edge cases, and a11y roles/labels.
- Avoid implementation details; assert on behavior and DOM.
- Prefer role/name queries, e.g. getByRole; avoid brittle hardcoded strings if translated.
- Use the component name in the describe and use "it" over "test" for better readability.
- Keep tests focused - 10-15 tests covering core functionality is better than 50+ over-detailed tests

## Mocking Strategy
- **Check global mocks first** - `i18nReact` is already mocked in `jest.init.js`
- **Mock only what's necessary** - Internal components, not external UI libraries
- **Use real cuix components** - Most work fine in tests, no need to mock
- **Mock internal dependencies** - Components from the same app/feature
- **Avoid excessive mocking** - Let real components work when possible


## Example
```ts
// Mock only internal dependencies, not external UI libraries
jest.mock('./InternalComponent', () => {
  return function MockInternalComponent(props: { title?: string }) {
    return <div data-testid="internal-component">{props.title}</div>;
  };
});

describe('PageHeader', () => {
  const defaultProps = {
    title: 'Test Title',
    onRefresh: jest.fn(),
    loading: false
  };

  beforeEach(() => {
    jest.clearAllMocks();
  });

  it('renders with title', () => {
    render(<PageHeader {...defaultProps} />);
    
    expect(screen.getByRole('heading', { level: 3 })).toHaveTextContent('Test Title');
  });

  it('calls onRefresh when refresh button is clicked', async () => {
    const user = userEvent.setup();
    const onRefresh = jest.fn();

    render(<PageHeader {...defaultProps} onRefresh={onRefresh} />);

    await user.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /refresh/i }));
    expect(onRefresh).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
  });

  it('disables refresh button when loading', () => {
    render(<PageHeader {...defaultProps} loading={true} />);
    
    expect(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /refresh/i })).toBeDisabled();
  });

  it('returns null when no content to render', () => {
    const { container } = render(<PageHeader title={undefined} />);
    
    expect(container.firstChild).toBeNull();
  });
});
```

## Troubleshooting
- **ES Module errors**: Check if the component uses cuix/antd - don't mock them
- **i18n not working**: It's already mocked globally, remove local mocks
- **Tests timing out**: Make sure to await user interactions
- **Can't find elements**: Use `screen.debug()` to see the rendered DOM

# Executing tests
```shell
# Run all tests
npm run test
npm run test-coverage
npm run test-clearCache
# Run a single file
npm test -- --testPathPattern=WelcomeTour
npm test -- desktop/core/src/desktop/js/sidePanelViewModel.test.js
# Run tests with verbose output
npm test -- --verbose
# Run tests and show console output
npm test -- --verbose --silent=false
# Run tests and stop on first failure
npm test -- --bail
```
